\u00e9MON in trouble to breathe."},{"version":"firered","text":"When it plays in water, it rolls up its elongated ears to prevent their insides from getting wet."},{"version":"leafgreen","text":"By keeping still and listening intently, it can even tell what is in wild, fast-moving rivers."},{"version":"diamond","text":"It lives in rivers and lakes. In water, its coloring and patterns trick the vision of foes."},{"version":"pearl","text":"Its long ears are superb sensors. It can distinguish the movements of living things on riverbeds."},{"version":"platinum","text":"It can spend all day in water, since it can inhale and store a large volume of air."},{"version":"heartgold","text":"By keeping still and listening intently, it can tell what is in even wild, fast-moving rivers."},{"version":"soulsilver","text":"When it plays in water, it rolls up its elongated ears to prevent their insides from getting wet."},{"version":"black","text":"It can spend all day in water, since it can inhale and store a large volume of air."},{"version":"white","text":"It can spend all day in water, since it can inhale and store a large volume of air."},{"version":"black-2","text":"Its long ears are superb sensors. It can distinguish the movements of things in water and tell what they are."},{"version":"white-2","text":"Its long ears are superb sensors. It can distinguish the movements of things in water and tell what they are."},{"version":"x","text":"Its long ears are superb sensors. It can distinguish the movements of living things on riverbeds."},{"version":"y","text":"The bubble-like pattern on its stomach helps it camouflage itself when it\u2019s in the water."},{"version":"omega-ruby","text":"Azumarill\u2019s long ears are indispensable sensors. By focusing its hearing, this Pok\u00e9mon can identify what kinds of prey are around, even in rough and fast-running rivers."},{"version":"alpha-sapphire","text":"Azumarill can make balloons out of air. It makes these air balloons if it spots a